        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued April 2 at 3:31PM EDT until April 2 at 3:45PM EDT by NWS Pittsburgh PA</headline>
        <description>At 331 PM EDT, severe thunderstorms were located along a line from
16 miles southeast of Black Lick to near Ligonier, or along a line
from 17 miles southeast of Homer City to 9 miles southeast of
Latrobe, moving east at 50 mph.

HAZARD...Ping pong ball size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...People and animals outdoors will be injured. Expect
damage to roofs, siding, windows, and vehicles.

Locations impacted include...
Ligonier, Laurel Mountain and Laurel Mountain State Park.
</description>
        <instruction>Seek shelter inside a well-built structure and stay away from
windows. These storms are capable of producing large hail.</instruction>
